Biography

2021 – Cal State Monterey Bay

Will serve as a team co-captain with Sam Chavez.

Played in 63 sets while starting 16 of her 18 appearances.

Is CSUMB’s top returning attacker with a .286 attack percentage.

Is CSUMB’s top returner in block solos (7), assists (46) and total blocks (53).

Finished No. 9 in the CCAA with a 0.84 bps average.

Enters the season ranked No. 3 in CSUMB career attack percentage (.285).

Enters the season ranked No. 20 in CSUMB career block assists (100).

Posted five matches of double–figure kills.

Matched her career high with 13 kills against Stanislaus State (Oct. 23).

Matched her career high with six blocks against Stanislaus State (Oct. 23) and Cal State East Bay (Nov. 12).

Matched her career high with two aces against Cal Poly Humboldt (Oct. 29) and Cal State San Marcos (Nov. 13).

2019 – Cal State Monterey Bay

Appeared in 24 of 25 matches and 89 of 96 sets as a true freshman.

Hit a team season–high .476 (12–2–21) at Sonoma State (Oct. 2).

Reached double figures in kills five times.

Career–high 13 kills came at Stanislaus State (Sept. 21).

Only Jenna Tobin posted more points in a 4–set match than the season–high 16.5 Mollin had at Stanislaus State (Sept. 21).

Reached double digits in points eight times.

Matched her season high with 6.0 blocks against Concordia–Portland (Sept. 6) and Cal State San Marcos (Oct. 5).

Served her first 2 collegiate aces against Chico State (Oct. 12).

High School

A 4–time All–Tri-County Athletic League pick at Salesian Prep.

First team All–TCAL as a senior.

Led the Pride to the 2018 TCAL championship.

Also earned all–league honors in soccer.

Played club with Absolute VBC.

Personal

Is majoring in business administration with a concentration in management and international business.

Named to the CCAA Fall All–Academic Team for 2020.

Is a National Honor Society member.

Uncle Mark Helfrich is was the head football coach at Oregon and currently serves as an NFL analyst for Fox Sports.

Cousin Gabby Leo is a setter at UoP.

Parents are Sheila and John Helfrich.
